# zget Frontend Modernization: The Native Component Architecture

> **Philosophy**: Zero build steps. Zero frameworks. 100% Browser Standards.
> **Date**: January 3, 2026

## The Vision
We aren't just cleaning code; we're building a **forward-looking, specification-compliant PWA** that runs directly in the browser. 

No webpack, no vite, no node_modules hell. Just pure, unadulterated web standards.

## Architecture Overview

### 1. The Core (Lightweight Shell)
`index.html` becomes a tiny semantic shell (< 100 lines). Its only job is to:
1. Load critical CSS variables (Theme)
2. Register the Service Worker
3. Load the `AppRouter` component

### 2. The Router (Client-Side)
A custom `<zget-app>` component that handles:
- URL routing (History API)
- View switching (Lazy loading modules)
- Global state container (Pub/Sub pattern)

### 3. The Components (Shadow DOM)
Each major feature becomes a self-contained module.

| Component | File | Responsibility |
|-----------|------|----------------|
| `<zget-app>` | [components/app.js](file:///Users/base/Projects/zget/src/zget/server/static/components/app.js) | Router, State, Layout |
| `<zget-vault>` | [components/vault.js](file:///Users/base/Projects/zget/src/zget/server/static/components/vault.js) | Main library grid |
| `<zget-regions>` | [components/regions.js](file:///Users/base/Projects/zget/src/zget/server/static/components/regions.js) | Region status & grouping |
| `<zget-player>` | [components/player.js](file:///Users/base/Projects/zget/src/zget/server/static/components/player.js) | Video playback & control |
| `<zget-queue>` | `components/queue.js` | Download status & history |

## Modern Features (2026 Standards)

### 1. CSS Module Scripts
We will use **Constructable Stylesheets** to share styles efficiently between Shadow DOM boundaries without duplication.

```javascript
import sharedStyles from '../styles/shared.css' with { type: 'css' };

class ZgetComponent extends HTMLElement {
  connectedCallback() {
    const shadow = this.attachShadow({mode: 'open'});
    shadow.adoptedStyleSheets = [sharedStyles];
  }
}
```

### 2. Reactive Attributes
Components will observe their own attributes. Change `<zget-player src="...">` and it automatically re-renders.

### 3. Event-Driven Communication
- **Down**: Unidirectional data flow via properties
- **Up**: Custom DOM Events bubbles for actions (`<zget-item @play-video="...">`)

## Implementation Steps

### Phase 1: The Foundation
- [ ] Create [src/zget/server/static/styles/theme.css](file:///Users/base/Projects/zget/src/zget/server/static/styles/theme.css) (Variables)
- [ ] Create [src/zget/server/static/styles/shared.css](file:///Users/base/Projects/zget/src/zget/server/static/styles/shared.css) (Common components)
- [ ] Create [src/zget/server/static/components/base.js](file:///Users/base/Projects/zget/src/zget/server/static/components/base.js) (Base class helper)

### Phase 2: The Core Components
- [ ] Implement `<zget-app>` (Router)
- [ ] Implement `<zget-vault>` (Library Grid)
- [ ] Implement `<zget-player>` (Modal Player)

### Phase 3: Regions & Site Registry
- [ ] Refactor `<zget-regions>` to use `/api/regions` and `/api/regions/{id}`
- [ ] Implement interactive region selection and site listing
- [ ] Add loading and error states for regional data

### Phase 4: Backend Optimization
- [ ] Add `/api/video/{id}` to [app.py](file:///Users/base/Projects/zget/src/zget/server/app.py) for efficient metadata retrieval
- [ ] Update `<zget-app>` to use the new endpoint

### Phase 5: Verification & Cleanup
- [ ] Verify all components work together
- [ ] Delete legacy `index.html` logic (already mostly done)
- [ ] Audit for remaining `onclick` or inline JS

## Directory Structure

```
static/
├── index.html            # The Entry Point
├── service-worker.js     # The Offline Engine
├── styles/
│   ├── theme.css         # --primary: #FFD54F;
│   └── shared.css        # Buttons, Inputs, Cards
└── components/
    ├── app.js            # The Orchestrator
    ├── base.js           # The helper class
    ├── vault.js          # The Library
    ├── regions.js        # The Regions
    └── player.js         # The Player
```

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- N/A (Frontend components require browser verification)

### Manual Verification
1. **Regions View**:
   - Navigate to 'Regions'.
   - Verify region cards load with correct stats (working/failed/untested).
   - Click a region and verify sites list is displayed with correct statuses.
2. **Video Player**:
   - Navigate to 'Vault'.
   - Click 'WATCH' on a video card.
   - Verify player modal opens and video starts playing.
   - Verify player fetches metadata efficiently (via Network tab).
3. **Responsive Audit**:
   - Check UI on mobile breakpoints (375px width).
   - Verify glassmorphism effects and scrolling performance.
